[1.543, "o", "\u001b[3;90m# Use `jsn updateset use` or `jsn scope use` to change scope/updateset\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1;90mPROFILE USER   [SCOPE]  UPDATE SET\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b]8;;https://dev373698.service-now.com\u001b\\pdi    \u001b]8;;\u001b\\ \u001b]8;;https://dev373698.service-now.com/sys_user_list.do?sysparm_query=sys_id=6816f79cc0a8016401c5a33be04be441\u001b\\System\u001b]8;;\u001b\\ \u001b]8;;https://dev373698.service-now.com/sys_scope.do?sysparm_query=scope=global\u001b\\[global]\u001b]8;;\u001b\\ \u001b]8;;https://dev373698.service-now.com/sys_update_set.do?sys_id=7dba58ecf54403100a22c0b3dfa151af\u001b\\Default\u001b]8;;\u001b\\\r\n"]
[0.615, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;38;2;232;162;23mQuery Operators\u001b[0m\r\n\r\nA comprehensive reference of query operators used across all ServiceNow query APIs\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mQuery Operators\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mQuery Operators\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  These operators are used across all ServiceNow query APIs to filter and retrieve records. They work consistently whether you're using:\r\n  - **[GlideRecord](/docs/gliderecord/)** – The standard server-side API for database operations\r\n  - **[GlideRecordSecure](/docs/gliderecordsecure/)** – GlideRecord with ACL enforcement\r\n  - **[GlideQuery](/docs/glidequery/)** – The modern, expressive alternative to GlideRecord\r\n  - **[GlideAggregate](/docs/glideaggregate/)** – For database aggregation queries (COUNT, SUM, MIN, MAX, AVG)\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mUsing Operators\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mIn GlideRecord & GlideRecordSecure\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  Use operators with `addQuery()` or `addEncodedQuery()`:\r\n  var gr = new GlideRecord('incident');\r\n  gr.addQuery('priority', '<=', 2);\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  gr.addQuery('state', 'IN', '1,2');\r\n  gr.query();\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mIn GlideQuery\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  Pass operators as the second argument in `where()`:\r\n  new GlideQuery('incident')\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  .where('priority', '<=', 2)\r\n  .where('state', 'IN', [1, 2])\r\n  .select();\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1mIn GlideAggregate\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  Operators work the same as GlideRecord:\r\n  var ga = new GlideAggregate('incident');\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  ga.addQuery('priority', '<=', 2);\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  ga.addAggregate('COUNT');\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  ga.query();\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  ---\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mOperator Reference\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  | Operator label           | Equivalent query operator | Example query                                                                 |\r\n  | ------------------------ | ------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n  | is not                   | `!=`                      | `short_description!=Network storage unavailable`                              |\r\n  | and                      | `^`                       | `active=true^CallerISNOTEMPTY`                                                |\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  | OR filter (new query)    | `^NQ`                     | `active=true^NQactive=false`                                                  |\r\n  | OR condition             | `^OR`                     | `short_descriptionISEMPTY^ORdescriptionISEMPTY`                               |\r\n"]
